The paper introduces a new data structure for efficient search in FM indices, which is a fundamental data structure in bioinformatics. The paper focuses on the space and time efficiency of the data structure, which suggests that it belongs to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also mentions applications in read mapping, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), computational biology (cs.CB), and databases (cs.DB).
